NUMBER 1470
NAME Forest Clearing
FOREST
DAY_LIGHT
CALL 33
*DESCRIPTION_START
You have entered the woods surrounding the Forester's Grove, and its
beauty and vibrant health enfold you. An over all sense of rightness, of
nature living and thriving with only minor tending by mankind exists here,
and throughout the forest. The sounds of life are heard throughout, 
regardless of the time.
*DESCRIPTION_END
EXIT S 568
IFVERB SEARCH -1
  IFVAR RAC = 2
    ECHO PLAYER You sense the handiwork of your own kind nearby, and searching about, discover a trail leading through the forest in a northeasterly direction.
    IFNOITEM 8
      NEWITEM 8 76 VAL2=1471 
    ENDIF
  ELSE
    IFVAR ORG = 27
      ECHO PLAYER You search around, and discover an aelven trail, leading in a northeasterly direction.
      IFNOITEM 8
        NEWITEM 8 76 VAL2=1471 
      ENDIF
    ELSE
      IFVAR SKILL17 > 10
        ECHO PLAYER Your affinity to druidic magic allows you to discover an aelven trail that leads in a northeasterly direction.
        IFNOITEM 8
          NEWITEM 8 76 VAL2=1471 
        ENDIF
      ELSE
        IFVAR SKILL18 > 5
          ECHO PLAYER You skill in woodlore allows you to discover an aelven trail leading in a northeasterly direction.
          IFNOITEM 8
            NEWITEM 8 76 VAL2=1471 
          ENDIF 
        ELSE
          ECHO PLAYER You find nothing remarkable.
        ENDIF
      ENDIF
    ENDIF
  ENDIF
ENDIF
IFPREVERB CLIMB 8
  CLEARVERB
  ECHO ALL %P disappears into the trees.
  REMOVEITEM -1
  AFFECT 1471 
  ECHO OTHERS %P arrives down a small trail.
  AFFECT 1470
  MOVEGROUP 1471
ENDIF
;
NUMBER 1471
NAME Forest Trail
FOREST
DAY_LIGHT
CALL 33
*DESCRIPTION_START
This small, snow covered path winds its way past trees, affording
fantastic views of the forest floor in wintertime. Small bushes 
decorated with icicles, while snow laden limbs of trees above peek
out over the trail. All sights and sounds of civilization seem
to have been left behind as you follow the aelfen trail through
the trees. Far to the northeast, a crick seems to pace its way
next to the trail.
*DESCRIPTION_END
EXIT NE 1473
ITEM 0 76 VAL2=1470
;
NUMBER 1473
NAME Forest Trail, Crick 
FOREST
DAY_LIGHT
CALL 33
*DESCRIPTION_START
A small babbling crick paces you for several hundred yards here, 
kept unfrozen by its fast current. Above, you can see an empty nest
left over from summertime by a pair of birds. Numerous animal
tracks cross the trail in places. Overall, a sense of peace
and tranquility fills you.
*DESCRIPTION_END
EXIT NE 1474
EXIT SW 1471
;
NUMBER 1474
NAME Forest Trail
FOREST
DAY_LIGHT
CALL 33
*DESCRIPTION_START
In the far distance, you hear the sound of a running crick, but otherwise
this area seems quiet. Snow-covered trees, bare of their leaves hang
close over the path, as if trying to block your view. A prevading sense
of watching is felt throughout the area.
*DESCRIPTION_END
EXIT E 1353
EXIT SW 1473
;
NUMBER 1353
NAME Forest Trail
FOREST
DAY_LIGHT
CALL 33
*DESCRIPTION_START
This small winding trail exists deep in the forest northeast of Fayd. All 
around are the sounds of animals and wildlife. Dense, old trees are grouped
carefully, and many look as if they are well tended, yet no signs of
human life exist past the trail. Ahead, lies a small clearing with
the makings of a vale beyond it. A smaller trail disappears into the nearby
trees.
*DESCRIPTION_END
EXIT W 1474
EXIT N 1714
ITEM 0 76 ADJ1=210 VAL2=1354
;narrow trail
EXTEND 0 leading into a secluded wooded vale
ITEM 1 229 
ITEM 9 693
IFPREVERB GAZE -1
  CLEARVERB
  IFVAR SKILL18 > 10 
    IFVAR RAC = 2
      IFVAR SKILL18 < 25
        ECHO PLAYER You catch glimpses of aelven guards secretly watching the area.
        ECHO OTHERS %N gazes around the area.
      ELSE 
	ECHO PLAYER You see a small group of aelven guard armed with bows watching over the area.
        ECHO OTHERS %N gazes around the area.
      ENDIF
    ELSE 
      ECHO PLAYER You feel like you are being watched.
    ENDIF
  ELSE
    ECHO PLAYER You gaze around the area.
    ECHO OTHERS %N gazes around the area.
  ENDIF
ENDIF 
IFPREVERB LISTEN -1
  CLEARVERB
  IFVAR RAC = 2
    ECHO PLAYER You hear several bird signals.
  ELSE
    ECHO PLAYER You hear the movements of the forest and birds chirping.
  ENDIF
ENDIF
