NUMBER 1354
NAME Chlry'est, Entrance
FOREST
DAY_LIGHT
CALL 33
*DESCRIPTION_START
In between two huge oak trees, the trail continues, and leads to 
this open area. The woods are quiet, and yet, still full of sound. 
Somewhere nearby the sound of a small crick can be heard bubbling over
its bed of rocks. A ladder leads up the base of a nearby tree.
*DESCRIPTION_END
ITEM 0 76 ADJ1=210 VAL2=1353
;narrow trail
EXTEND 0 leading out of the vale
ITEM 1 335 ADJ1=355 VAL2=1355
ITEM 9 693
;***NEWBIE AELF STUFF
IFENTRY -1
  IFVAR LEV > 10
    EQUAL INTNUM6 10
  ENDIF
  IFVAR INTNUM6 = 5
    EQUAL ROUNDTIME 22
    PLREVENT 1
    CONTPLREVENT 
    ECHO PLAYER A young aelven lass with short, blonde hair and dark brown eyes climbs down from a nearby ladder and smiles at you.
    ECHO PLAYER She says, "Welcome to Chlry'est traveler. I am always happy to meet a new face."
    PLREVENT 3
    CONTPLREVENT
    ECHO PLAYER She continues, "Let me show you around, and teach you some of our ways before you continue upon your journey."
    ECHO PLAYER She smiles warmly at you, and then gestures towards the ladder she had just climbed down.
    PLREVENT 3
    CONTPLREVENT
    ECHO PLAYER She grins, and says, "We might as well start at the top. I am C'ven'ti, and Chlry'est is my home. I am a aelf much like yourself. Here, CLIMB this ladder and we shall continue."
    PLREVENT 3
    CONTPLREVENT
    ECHO PLAYER She leans over and whispers to you, "We must pass through the guards, but don't worry, they know me."
  ENDIF
ENDIF
IFPREVERB GO 0
  IFVAR INTNUM6 < 10
    CLEARVERB
    ECHO PLAYER C'ven'ti looks oddly at you, and gestures towards the ladder. "Shouldn't you come this way first?"
  ENDIF
ENDIF
;
NUMBER 1355
NAME Chlry'est, Guard House
INDOOR_FLOOR
OBSCURED_DAY_LIGHT
CALL 33
*DESCRIPTION_START
Inside this small building, you realize you've passed into the heart
of the tree. The heart wood thrums with life and you hear the soft sounds
of living animals moving throughout the tree itself. Numerous small 
openings give glimpses of the woods around. A ladder leads down to the ground.
*DESCRIPTION_END
EXIT SE 1365
ITEM 0 335 ADJ1=355 VAL2=1354
ITEM 1 72 
ITEM 2 72
ITEM 3 72
ITEM 9 693
;***NEWBIE STUFF
IFENTRY -1
  IFVAR LEV > 10
    EQUAL INTNUM6 10
  ENDIF
  IFVAR INTNUM6 = 5
    EQUAL ROUNDTIME 10
    PLREVENT 1
    CONTPLREVENT
    ECHO PLAYER C'ven'ti gestures towards the tree around you. "See how we preserve life? A true aelf of the forest never seeks to harm it. We blend our lives and our desires around Nature herself. Nothing we add to the land can make it more lovely than it already is."
    PLREVENT 3
    CONTPLREVENT
    ECHO PLAYER She continues, "This tree for instance, we simply borrow the space within it. We aren't harming it. Aelves are caretakers of the land more than any other species."
    ECHO PLAYER She gestures to the SOUTHEAST (SE). "If you walk this way, we shall continue."
    EQUAL INTNUM6 6
  ENDIF
ENDIF
IFPREVERB GO 0
  IFVAR INTNUM6 < 10
    CLEARVERB
    ECHO PLAYER C'ven'ti gazes at you, and says, "Why are you going that way?" 
  ENDIF
ENDIF
IFPREVERB CLIMB 0
  IFVAR INTNUM6 < 10
    CLEARVERB
    ECHO PLAYER C'ven'ti gazes at you, and says, "Why are you going that way?" 
  ENDIF
ENDIF
