NUMBER 1396
NAME Chlry'est, Gathering
INDOOR_FLOOR
FIXED_LIGHT
CALL 33
*DESCRIPTION_START
This large area has been meshed so completely with the tree, that it is
extremely hard to tell where nature leaves off, and aelf has continued.
Long, low benches have been lovingly worked from oak, rosewood and maple,
and line the outer edges. Only a small, decorative railing sits
near the edge of the platform. Several ornate chairs have been placed randomly
around the chamber, each pleasing to the eye and heart. The boughs
above creak softly with each breath of air, almost as if the tree herself 
talks to you from her winter sleep. Down below, through the bare limbs of the
trees, a training area can be seen with practice dummies.
*DESCRIPTION_END
EXIT D 1426
EXIT W 1365
ITEM 0 339
ITEM 1 86 ADJ1=355
ITEM 2 607
ITEM 3 335 VAL2=1404 
ITEM 4 335 VAL2=1405
ITEM 5 61 VAL2=1463
ITEM 6 72 VAL2=201
ITEM 9 693
;****NEWBIE STUFF
IFENTRY -1
  IFVAR LEV > 10
    EQUAL INTNUM6 10
  ENDIF
  IFVAR INTNUM6 = 6
    EQUAL ROUNDTIME 165
    PLREVENT 0
    CONTPLREVENT
    ECHO PLAYER C'ven'ti beams happily, and gestures at the gathering hall. "It is here we come to sit and tell stories, dance, sing, and share our lives. This is our Gathering Hall. Perhaps one of the story tellers shall recite a story or two?"
    PLREVENT 3
    CONTPLREVENT
    ECHO PLAYER C'ven'ti gazes about the room, and spies a very old aelf relaxing against the far railing. "Ah, we shall ask Dem'oltry. He always enjoys travelers such as yourself. Notice, how old he seems. It is rare for our kind to age rapidly. We are just leaving our homes at the age of 70 years!"
    PLREVENT 4
    CONTPLREVENT
    ECHO PLAYER "Dem'oltry! Come tell us a story. This young traveler seeks to learn our ways."
    ECHO PLAYER The old aelf strolls over slowly, looking you up and down. "Ye be an aelf, what do ye mean learn our ways? I suspect this young one only needs to be reminded." He smiles warmly at you.
    PLREVENT 4
    CONTPLREVENT
    ECHO PLAYER "Well then, I shall tell you a story of battle, then one of truth, and finally I shall tell you of our Creeds."
    PLREVENT 4
    CONTPLREVENT
    ECHO PLAYER Dem'oltry begins his tale of battle....
    ECHO PLAYER "Ages ago, when the human city of Fayd was new, aelves joined with the wolflings in effort to stop the Dark Ones and the werewolves from destroying the forests and the city itself."
    PLREVENT 4
    CONTPLREVENT
    ECHO PLAYER "Aelves and wolflings joined, and in a fierce battle, we finally drove off the foul Mardhrel and weres... and the city and forest were preserved."
    ECHO PLAYER "Remember, we may not choose battle over peace .. but when the issue is forced, we are much fiercer than our foes worst nightmares."
    PLREVENT 5
    CONTPLREVENT
    ECHO PLAYER He pauses, taking a drink of wine. "Now, a tale of truth.."
    ECHO PLAYER "Long ago, when we first came into being, our kind was that of magic. We thrived in it, and it fed us and our way of being. But then, we began to argue amongst ourselves."
    PLREVENT 5
    CONTPLREVENT
    ECHO PLAYER "Some of us decided to stay and teach humans of our ways to prevent the land from being damaged. Others, decided to retreat underground, and have nothing further to do with humans and the other races. The 'light' aelves favored joining with the humans, and becoming caretakers of the earth, while the Mardhrel crept below the earth, and delved deeply into the arcane arts."
    PLREVENT 5
    CONTPLREVENT
    ECHO PLAYER "Our two kinds have warred ever since, and the hatred between our races burns in our blood like nothing else."
    PLREVENT 4
    CONTPLREVENT
    ECHO PLAYER Dem'oltry sighs, and finally speaks again. "And now my traveling friend, I shall speak to you of our Creeds."
    ECHO PLAYER "A true aelf follows the path of Light, seeking out the guidance of Totems, or perhaps one of the gods of man. Those that follow the Dark paths have lost their way, and need guidance to return."
    PLREVENT 5
    CONTPLREVENT
    ECHO PLAYER "We take life not in pleasure, but in need, for we rejoice in life. We are not silly and carefree, but yet we find pleasure in the simple beauty of a budding rose, or a drop of rain."
    PLREVENT 5
    CONTPLREVENT
    ECHO PLAYER "Above all else, we value nature and her essence. It is this essence that gives us life and breath. Our souls sing when our feet trod the ways of the forest or meadow. Seek always such places, and you shall know comfort most of your life."
    PLREVENT 5
    CONTPLREVENT
    ECHO PLAYER "Our seeming agelessness and our dislike of the grotesque can be our downfalls, if our emotions are left to run amuck. Be wary young traveler in your journey. Perhaps these things might aid you."
    PLREVENT 4
    CONTPLREVENT
    ECHO PLAYER As Dem'oltry finishes, C'ven'ti steps forward and gives you several items. With a smile, she directs you towards an opening at the back of the room.
    NEWITEM -1 253 ADJ1=87 ADJ2=40 ADJ3=1
    NEWITEM -1 255 ADJ1=133 ADJ2=152
    NEWITEM -1 217 ADJ1=539 ADJ2=180
    EQUAL INTNUM6 10
    EQUAL FLAG1 1
    ECHO PLAYER The two aelves smile warmly at you, and wish you well on your travels.
  ENDIF
ENDIF
IFPREVERB GO 6
  IFVAR FLAG1 ! 1
    CLEARVERB
    ECHO PLAYER What are you referring to? Please be more specific.
  ENDIF
ENDIF
IFTOUCH 6
  IFVAR FLAG1 ! 1
    CLEARVERB
     ECHO PLAYER What are you referring to? Please be more specific.
  ENDIF
ENDIF
