NUMBER 1425
NAME Chlry'est, Training Grounds
FOREST
DAY_LIGHT
CALL 33
*DESCRIPTION_START
Below the shade of the trees lies this rudimentary practice yard.  Packed snow
around the target dummies hint at continuous honing of skills.  To the
north appears to be an archery range.  The practice grounds continue to the 
east. A barrel with practice equipment sits near a tree. 
*DESCRIPTION_END
ITEM 0 1704 ADJ1=355
EXTEND 0 covered with straw stuffed padding
ITEM 1 1032
EXTEND 1 full of wooden swords for practice
ITEM 2 1112 
*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM READ 2
This is a practice area for swordsmanship. Please pull a sword from the 
barrel, [Pull Barrel]. Then, attack the dummy. [Strike Dummy] You can
check on the status of the dummy, for when it will need restuffing simply by
looking at it. To restuff it, simply push the stuffing back inside. [Push Dummy].
*DESCRIPTION_END
ITEM 9 693
EXIT N 1426
EXIT U 1396
EXIT E 1443
IFPREVERB PULL 1
  CLEARVERB
  ECHO PLAYER You reach into the barrel and pull out a wooden sword.
  ECHO OTHERS %N reaches into the barrel and pulls out a wooden sword.
  NEWITEM -1 45 ADJ1=355
ENDIF
IFPREVERB STRIKE 0
  CLEARVERB 
  IFCARRY 45 355 
    IFITEM -1 WIELDED
      IFVAR FLAG2 > 5
        ECHO PLAYER You must first restuff the dummy.
      ELSE
        IFVAR GFLAG1 = 0
          EQUAL ROUNDTIME 5
          EQUAL GFLAG1 1
          ECHO PLAYER You lift your sword, and gaze at the practice dummy, planning your strike.
          ECHO OTHERS %N takes a long look at the practice target.                
          PLREVENT 1
          CONTPLREVENT
          EQUAL CHYMESWORD 0
          ECHO PLAYER You step forward with a spry manuever and get in place to swing at the dummy.
          ECHO PLAYER You lift your arm, preparing to strike...
          ECHO OTHERS %N spryly steps forward, and raises %h arm to strike the target dummy...
          RANDOM CHYMESWORD 1 50 0
          ADD CHYMESWORD SKILL13
          DIV CHYMESWORD 10
          IFVAR CHYMESWORD <= 1
            ECHO PLAYER You step forward, and with a mighty swing, you totally miss the target and bury your sword into the ground!
            ECHO OTHERS %N steps forward, and with a mighty swing, buries %h sword into the ground!
            PLREVENT 0
            CONTPLREVENT
            ECHO ALL %N bashfully pulls %h sword from the ground.
            EQUAL GFLAG1 0
          ENDIF
          IFVAR CHYMESWORD = 2
            ADD GFLAG2 1 
            ECHO PLAYER Your strike barely catches the outside of the target.
            ECHO OTHERS %N barely catches the outside of the target with a mighty swing.
            EQUAL GFLAG1 0
          ENDIF
          IFVAR CHYMESWORD = 3
            ADD GFLAG2 1 
            ECHO PLAYER You strike at the target, and your sword grazes off the shoulder of the dummy.
            ECHO OTHERS %N grazes the shoulder of the dummy with %h sword.
            EQUAL GFLAG1 0
          ENDIF
          IFVAR CHYMESWORD = 4
            ADD GFLAG2 1 
            ECHO PLAYER You begin a beautiful overhand strike, aiming for the exposed neck, but end up burying your blade into the straw shoulder.
            ECHO OTHERS %N starts a long overhand strike, and buries %h sword in the straw shoulder.
            EQUAL GFLAG1 0
          ENDIF           
          IFVAR CHYMESWORD = 5
            ADD GFLAG2 1 
            ECHO PLAYER You begin a delicate sweeping blow at what would be thighs, and elegantly lop off a straw leg at the knee.
            ECHO OTHERS %N swings at the lower half of the dummy, and takes off a large amount of straw.
            EQUAL GFLAG1 0
          ENDIF
          IFVAR CHYMESWORD = 6
            ADD GFLAG2 1 
            ECHO PLAYER You thrust at the dummy's chest with a sweeping motion, and slice a long gouge across the leather.
            ECHO OTHERS %N rips a long gouge out of the leather covering the dummy's chest.
            EQUAL GFLAG1 0 
          ENDIF
          IFVAR CHYMESWORD = 7
            ADD GFLAG2 1 
            ECHO PLAYER You leap towards the target, screaming loudly and land a solid blow into the stomach!
            ECHO OTHERS With a loud scream, %N leaps towards the target, and buries %h sword hilt deep in the stomach!
            AFFECT  1426
            ECHO ALL  You hear a primal scream of fury from the nearby training area.
            AFFECT 1443
            ECHO ALL  You hear a primal scream of fury from the nearby training area.
            AFFECT 1425 
            EQUAL GFLAG1 0
          ENDIF
          IFVAR CHYMESWORD = 8
            ADD GFLAG2 1 
            ECHO ALL The sword thunks into the very outside of the target's chest.
            EQUAL GFLAG1 0
          ENDIF
          IFVAR CHYMESWORD = 9  
            ADD GFLAG2 1 
            ECHO PLAYER With a practiced motion, you gently slide the sword to the hilt in the side of the dummy.
            ECHO OTHERS %N gracefully slides %h sword into the straw of the dummy.  
            EQUAL GFLAG1 0
          ENDIF
          IFVAR CHYMESWORD = 10
            ADD GFLAG2 1 
            ECHO PLAYER  You swing at the dummy, and make a passable attack, lobbing off a portion of the arm.
            ECHO OTHERS %N lands a good hit on one of the arms, straw goes flying.
            EQUAL GFLAG1 0
          ENDIF 
          IFVAR CHYMESWORD = 11
            ADD GFLAG2 1 
            ECHO ALL With a loud whistling sound, %N's blade swishes through the air, connecting with the dummy.
            EQUAL GFLAG1 0
          ENDIF
          IFVAR CHYMESWORD = 12
            ADD GFLAG2 1 
            ECHO PLAYER You make a wonderful thrust, and nearly split the dummy in two!
            ECHO OTHERS %N nearly cuts the dummy in two!
            EQUAL GFLAG1 0 
          ENDIF
          IFVAR CHYMESWORD => 13
              ECHO PLAYER You thrust at the dummy, and knock the head clean off at the shoulders!
              ECHO OTHERS What a great shot! %N decapitated the dummy!
              EQUAL GFLAG1 0
              EQUAL GFLAG2 7
           ENDIF  
        ELSE            
          ECHO PLAYER You must wait your turn to attack.
        ENDIF
      ENDIF
    ELSE
      ECHO PLAYER You have to wield your wooden sword first.
    ENDIF
  ELSE
    ECHO PLAYER You need to have a wooden sword first, get one in the barrel.
  ENDIF
ENDIF
IFPREVERB LOOK 0
  CLEARVERB
  IFVAR GFLAG2 > 0
     ECHO PLAYER The dummy is showing some signs of wear.
  ELSE  
     IFVAR GFLAG2 = 7
       ECHO PLAYER The dummy is missing its head.
     ENDIF
  ENDIF    
ENDIF
IFPREVERB PUSH 0
  CLEARVERB
  IFVAR GFLAG1 = 0        
    IFVAR GFLAG2 ! 0 
      EQUAL ROUNDTIME 5    
      EQUAL GFLAG2 0         
      ECHO PLAYER You begin to restuff the target with straw. 
      ECHO OTHERS %N begins to restuff the target with straw.
      PLREVENT 2
      CONTPLREVENT
      ECHO PLAYER You finish, and notice yourself beginning to itch inside your clothing.
      ECHO OTHERS %N finishes stuffing the target and moves out of the way making it clear to fight.
    ELSE
      ECHO PLAYER The target doesn't need stuffed at the moment.
    ENDIF
  ELSE
    ECHO PLAYER You might want to wait until they finish assaulting the target.
  ENDIF
ENDIF 
;
NUMBER 1426
NAME Chlry'est, Training Grounds
FOREST
DAY_LIGHT
CALL 33
*DESCRIPTION_START
This area is for the bow-weapon training. Numerous piles of
arrows and stacks of simple bows are available. To the south and southeast
lies two more training grounds. A barrel full of greatbows rests under
the shade of a tree. Snow has been tromped down or removed, allowing
ease of movement.
*DESCRIPTION_END
ITEM 0 1704 ADJ1=355
EXTEND 0 covered with straw stuffed padding with a bullseye painted on the chest
ITEM 9 693
ITEM 1 1032 
EXTEND 1 full of greatbows for training
ITEM 2 1112
*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM READ 2
This is an area for bow practice. Please pull a bow from the barrel. 
[Pull Barrel]. Then, line up your shot by pointing the bow down
the course at the dummy. [Point Dummy]. You will have to collect your
arrows periodically from the dummy, simply by pulling them free. [Pull 
Dummy]. Please be careful with your shots, for there are many folk
that use all areas of the training grounds.
*DESCRIPTION_END 
EXIT S 1425
EXIT SE 1443
IFPREVERB PULL 1
  CLEARVERB
  ECHO PLAYER You pull a wooden greatbow out of the barrel.
  ECHO OTHERS %N reaches into the barrel and removes a wooden greatbow.  
  NEWITEM -1 1476 ADJ1=355
ENDIF   
IFPREVERB STRIKE 0
  CLEARVERB
  ECHO PLAYER An instructer gazes at you, and says, "If you wish to use that sort of attack, go to the weapon area please."
  ECHO OTHERS An instructer gazes at %N, and says, "If you wish to use that sort of attack, go to the weapon area please."
ENDIF
IFPREVERB POINT 0
  CLEARVERB 
  IFCARRY 1476 355
    IFITEM -1 WIELDED
      IFVAR FLAG2 > 5
        ECHO PLAYER You must clear the target first.
      ELSE
        IFVAR GFLAG1 = 0
          EQUAL ROUNDTIME 5
          EQUAL GFLAG1 1
          ECHO ALL %N loads the greatbow with an arrow.
          PLREVENT 1
          CONTPLREVENT   
          ECHO PLAYER You take careful aim with the bow at the distant target.
          ECHO OTHERS %N takes careful aim with %h bow at the distant target.                
          PLREVENT 1
          CONTPLREVENT
          EQUAL CHYMEARROW 0
          ECHO PLAYER You gaze down the length of the shaft and home in on the center of the target
          ECHO PLAYER You release the arrow...
          ECHO PLAYER ...It goes screaming for its target.
          ECHO OTHERS %N slowly brings the bow up to firing position and takes aim at the target.  %N fires.    
          RANDOM CHYMEARROW 1 60 0
          ADD CHYMEARROW SKILL3
          DIV CHYMEARROW 10
          IFVAR CHYMEARROW <= 1
            ECHO PLAYER Your arrow flies wide of the target and goes out into the forest beyond.
            ECHO OTHERS %N misses the target completely.
            AFFECT 1425
            ECHO ALL An arrow comes wizzing into the room.
            AFFECT  1426
            PLREVENT 0
            CONTPLREVENT
            ECHO ALL You hear a shriek from the forest.
            EQUAL GFLAG1 0
          ENDIF
          IFVAR CHYMEARROW = 2
            ADD GFLAG2 1 
            ECHO PLAYER Your arrow barely catches the outside of the target.
            ECHO OTHERS %N barely catches the outside of the target.
            EQUAL GFLAG1 0
          ENDIF
          IFVAR CHYMEARROW = 3
            ADD GFLAG2 1 
            ECHO PLAYER The arrow lands just outside the outermost blue ring of the target.
            ECHO OTHERS %N sticks just at the outside of the outermost blue ring of the target.
            EQUAL GFLAG1 0
          ENDIF
          IFVAR CHYMEARROW = 4
            ADD GFLAG2 1 
            ECHO PLAYER The arrow lands firmly in the outer blue ring of the target.
            ECHO OTHERS %N lands the arrow firmly in the outer blue ring of the target.
            EQUAL GFLAG1 0
          ENDIF           
          IFVAR CHYMEARROW = 5
            ADD GFLAG2 1 
            ECHO PLAYER The arrow lands between the outside blue and inside yellow ring of the target.
            ECHO OTHERS %N lands the arrow between the blue and yellow rings of the target.
            EQUAL GFLAG1 0
          ENDIF
          IFVAR CHYMEARROW = 6
            ADD GFLAG2 1 
            ECHO PLAYER The arrow lands solidly in the yellow ring of the target.
            ECHO OTHERS %N lands the arrow firmly in the yellow ring of the target.
            EQUAL GFLAG1 0 
          ENDIF
          IFVAR CHYMEARROW = 7
            ADD GFLAG2 1 
            ECHO PLAYER The arrow lands between the inner yellow and bullseye of the target.
            ECHO OTHERS %N lands the arrow between inner yellow and bullseye of the target.
            EQUAL GFLAG1 0
          ENDIF
          IFVAR CHYMEARROW = 8
            ADD GFLAG2 1 
            ECHO ALL The arrow thunks into the very outside of the bullseye.
            EQUAL GFLAG1 0
          ENDIF
          IFVAR CHYMEARROW = 9  
            ADD GFLAG2 1 
            ECHO PLAYER The arrow flies a bit wildly at first, but finally plunks into the target, solidly in the bullseye, just off center.
            ECHO OTHERS %N lands the arrow in the bullseye, just off center however.  
            EQUAL GFLAG1 0
          ENDIF
          IFVAR CHYMEARROW = 10
            ADD GFLAG2 1 
            ECHO PLAYER The arrow lands at the top of the bullseye, barely inside the red.
            ECHO OTHERS %N lands the arrow at the top of the bullseye, barely inside the red.  
            EQUAL GFLAG1 0
          ENDIF 
          IFVAR CHYMEARROW = 11
            ADD GFLAG2 1 
            ECHO ALL The arrow buzzes at it flies towards the target, a bit of loose fletching. It smashes into the bullseye to the right.
            EQUAL GFLAG1 0
          ENDIF
          IFVAR CHYMEARROW = 12
            ADD GFLAG2 1 
            ECHO PLAYER The arrow thunks into the target within an inch of dead center.
            ECHO OTHERS %N lands the arrow almost exactly into the bullseye.
            EQUAL GFLAG1 0 
          ENDIF
          IFVAR CHYMEARROW => 13
            IFVAR GFLAG3 => 1
              ECHO PLAYER You split the arrow in the center!
              ECHO OTHERS What a great shot! %N split the arrow in the center!
              EQUAL GFLAG1 0
            ELSE
              ECHO PLAYER You hit the bullseye dead center! A better shot couldn't be made!
              ECHO OTHERS %N hit the bullseye dead center! A better shot couldn't be made!   
              ADD GFLAG2 1
              ADD GFLAG3 1   
              EQUAL GFLAG1 0
            ENDIF
          ENDIF  
        ELSE            
          ECHO PLAYER You must wait your turn to fire.
        ENDIF
      ENDIF
    ELSE
      ECHO PLAYER You need to wield your wooden greatbow.
    ENDIF
   ELSE
      ECHO PLAYER You need to get a wooden greatbow from the barrel.
   ENDIF
ENDIF
IFPREVERB LOOK 0
  CLEARVERB
  STRCVT 1 GFLAG2
  ECHO PLAYER Currently there are %1 arrows in the target.
  IFVAR GFLAG3 > 0
    ECHO PLAYER There is an arrow in the bullseye.
  ENDIF
ENDIF
IFPREVERB PULL 0
  CLEARVERB
  IFVAR GFLAG1 = 0
    IFVAR GFLAG2 ! 0 
      EQUAL ROUNDTIME 5           
      ECHO PLAYER You begin to clear all the arrows from the target. 
      ECHO OTHERS %N begins to clear the arrows from the target.
      PLREVENT 2
      CONTPLREVENT
      EQUAL GFLAG2 0
      EQUAL GFLAG3 0
      ECHO PLAYER You gather the arrows and move out of the way.
      ECHO OTHERS %N finishes gathering the arrows and moves out of the way making it clear to fire.
    ELSE
      ECHO PLAYER There are no arrows for you to retrieve.
    ENDIF
  ELSE
    ECHO PLAYER You might want to wait until they finish shooting.
  ENDIF
ENDIF
NUMBER 1443
NAME Chlry'est, Training Grounds
FOREST
DAY_LIGHT
CALL 33
*DESCRIPTION_START
This area the same as the others, it has the target dummies.  What makes this
room different is the pile of fist sized rocks that lies about 30 feet away
and the scattered rocks that lie around the target.
*DESCRIPTION_END
ITEM 0 1704
ITEM 1 411
;rocks
ITEM 2 1112
*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM READ 2
This is a Psionics training area, to work in coordinating your attacks to
your best advantage. Simply concentrate your efforts on the rocks in
front of you. [Concentrate rock]. Please remember to collect your
rocks periodically, so you and the next person always has a ready supply.
[Get Rock]. Also, be careful of your aim, for many folk use this area.
*DESCRIPTION_END
ITEM 9 693
EXIT W 1425
EXIT NW 1426
IFPREVERB CONCENTRATE 1
  CLEARVERB 
  IFVAR FLAG2 > 5
    ECHO PLAYER You must collect the rocks first.
  ELSE
    IFVAR GFLAG1 = 0
      EQUAL ROUNDTIME 5
      EQUAL GFLAG1 1
      ECHO PLAYER You clear your mind of all thought, and see only the rocks in front of you.
      ECHO OTHERS %N takes a deep breath and seems to be concentrating.                
      PLREVENT 1
      CONTPLREVENT
      EQUAL CHYMEPSI 0
      ECHO PLAYER You peer down the length of the course, and focus on the distant target. 
      ECHO PLAYER You lift a single rock with your mind, and fling it down the course!
      ECHO PLAYER ...It goes whistling through the air...
      ECHO OTHERS %N slowly lifts a rock in mid-air in front of %i, and mentally hurls it down the course at the target!
      RANDOM CHYMEPSI 1 50 0
      ADD CHYMEPSI SKILL26
      DIV CHYMEPSI 10
      IFVAR CHYMEPSI <= 1
        ECHO PLAYER The rock flies by the target, and hurls into a nearby area!
        ECHO OTHERS %N misses the target completely.
        AFFECT 1426      
        ECHO ALL A rock comes wizzing into the room!
        AFFECT  1443
        PLREVENT 0
        CONTPLREVENT
        ECHO ALL A voice shouts out, "Hey watch it with the rocks!"
        EQUAL GFLAG1 0
      ENDIF
      IFVAR CHYMEPSI = 2
        ADD GFLAG2 1 
        ECHO PLAYER Your rock barely catches the outside of the target, smacking into the wooden dummy.
        ECHO OTHERS %N barely catches the outside of the target.
        EQUAL GFLAG1 0
      ENDIF
      IFVAR CHYMEPSI = 3
        ADD GFLAG2 1 
        ECHO PLAYER The rock lands just outside the outermost blue ring of the target.
        ECHO OTHERS %N's rock smacks just at the outside of the outermost blue ring of the target.
        EQUAL GFLAG1 0
      ENDIF
      IFVAR CHYMEPSI = 4
        ADD GFLAG2 1 
        ECHO PLAYER The rock lands hits firmly against the outer blue ring of the target.
        ECHO OTHERS %N lands the rock firmly against the outer blue ring of the target.
        EQUAL GFLAG1 0
      ENDIF           
      IFVAR CHYMEPSI = 5
        ADD GFLAG2 1 
        ECHO PLAYER The rock hits between the outside blue and inside yellow ring of the target.
        ECHO OTHERS %N lands the rock between the blue and yellow rings of the target.
        EQUAL GFLAG1 0
      ENDIF
      IFVAR CHYMEPSI = 6
        ADD GFLAG2 1 
        ECHO PLAYER The rock lands solidly on the yellow ring of the target.
        ECHO OTHERS %N lands the rock firmly on the yellow ring of the target.
        EQUAL GFLAG1 0 
      ENDIF
      IFVAR CHYMEPSI = 7
        ADD GFLAG2 1 
        ECHO PLAYER The stone lands between the inner yellow and bullseye of the target.
        ECHO OTHERS %N lands the stone between inner yellow and bullseye of the target.
        EQUAL GFLAG1 0
      ENDIF
      IFVAR CHYMEPSI = 8
        ADD GFLAG2 1 
        ECHO ALL The rock thunks against the very outside of the bullseye, carving a huge chunk from the wooden target.
        EQUAL GFLAG1 0
      ENDIF
      IFVAR CHYMEPSI = 9  
        ADD GFLAG2 1 
        ECHO PLAYER The stone wobbles a bit at first, but finally plunks against the target, solidly on the bullseye, just off center.
        ECHO OTHERS %N lands the rock on the bullseye, just off center however.  
        EQUAL GFLAG1 0
      ENDIF
      IFVAR CHYMEPSI = 10
        ADD GFLAG2 1 
        ECHO PLAYER The rock hits at the top of the bullseye, barely inside the red.
        ECHO OTHERS %N lands the rock at the top of the bullseye, barely inside the red.  
        EQUAL GFLAG1 0
      ENDIF 
      IFVAR CHYMEPSI = 11
        ADD GFLAG2 1 
        ECHO ALL The arrow buzzes at it flies towards the target, a bit of loose fletching. It smashes into the bullseye to the right.
        EQUAL GFLAG1 0
      ENDIF
      IFVAR CHYMEPSI = 12
        ADD GFLAG2 1 
        ECHO PLAYER The stone thunks into the target dead center.
        ECHO OTHERS %N lands the stone directly dead center.
        EQUAL GFLAG1 0 
      ENDIF
      IFVAR CHYMEPSI => 13
        ECHO PLAYER You hit the bullseye dead center! A better shot couldn't be made!
        ECHO OTHERS %N hit the bullseye dead center! A better shot couldn't be made!   
        ADD GFLAG2 1
        ADD GFLAG3 1   
        EQUAL GFLAG1 0
      ENDIF  
    ELSE            
      ECHO PLAYER You must wait your turn to go.
    ENDIF
  ENDIF
ENDIF
IFPREVERB LOOK 0
  CLEARVERB
  STRCVT 2 GFLAG2
  ECHO PLAYER Currently there are %2 stones under the target.
  IFVAR GFLAG3 > 0
    ECHO PLAYER There is a mark on the bullseye.
  ENDIF
ENDIF
IFPREVERB GET 1
  CLEARVERB
  IFVAR GFLAG1 = 0
    IFVAR GFLAG2 ! 0 
      EQUAL ROUNDTIME 5           
      ECHO PLAYER You begin to clear all the stones from under the target. 
      ECHO OTHERS %N begins to clear the stones from under the target.
      PLREVENT 2
      CONTPLREVENT
      EQUAL GFLAG2 0
      EQUAL GFLAG3 0
      ECHO PLAYER You gather the stones and move out of the way.
      ECHO OTHERS %N finishes gathering the stones and moves out of the way making it clear to fire.
    ELSE
      ECHO PLAYER There are no stones for you to retrieve.
    ENDIF
  ELSE
    ECHO PLAYER You might want to wait until they finish mentally heaving rocks down the course.
  ENDIF
ENDIF
